hina_260513/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Here&#39;s what&#39;s on Trump&#39;s to-do list in China</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/shorts/here-s-what-s-on-trump-s-to-do-list-in-china-263233093918"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/haake_ceos-mtqpm8.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">Here&#39;s what&#39;s on Trump&#39;s to-do list in China</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/haake_ceos-mtqpm8.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:09:08 GMT</pubDate><title>Here&#39;s what&#39;s on Trump&#39;s to-do list in China</title><updateDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 13:41:50 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:10:56 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The South Carolina Supreme Court has overturned Alex Murdaugh&#39;s double murder conviction and ordered a new trial in the killings of his wife and son. NBC News&#39; Laura Jarrett reports on the court&#39;s decision and what comes next for Murdaugh.</description><expires>2056-05-13T15:09:51.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/court-overturns-alex-murdaugh-s-murder-convictions-and-orders-new-trial-263240773797</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Court overturns Alex Murdaugh&#39;s murder convictions and orders new trial</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/court-overturns-alex-murdaugh-s-murder-convictions-and-orders-new-trial-263240773797"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778684977251_now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513_S3_1920x1080-5ver1o.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">The South Carolina Supreme Court has overturned Alex Murdaugh&#39;s double murder conviction and ordered a new trial in the killings of his wife and son. NBC News&#39; Laura Jarrett reports on the court&#39;s decision and what comes next for Murdaugh.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778684977251_now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778684977251_now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778684977251_now_brk_murdaugh_overturn_260513_S3_1920x1080-5ver1o.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:09:47 GMT</pubDate><title>Court overturns Alex Murdaugh&#39;s murder convictions and orders new trial</title><updateDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:10:56 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Lawrence Hurley</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 13 May 2026 16:45:32 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Supreme Court has admonished judges not to interfere in election cases when the process is underway, but it is being accused of doing that in redistricting decisions.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/supreme-court/supreme-court-criticism-redistricting-law-election-2026-voting-rights-rcna344734</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/supreme-court/supreme-court-criticism-redistricting-law-election-2026-voting-rights-rcna344734</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260317-john-roberts-judge-ch-1235-bb01cc.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Graeme Sloan</media:credit><media:text type="plain">John Roberts.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Chief Justice John Roberts recently complained that Americans view the justices as &#34;political actors.&#34;</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260317-john-roberts-judge-ch-1235-bb01cc.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 16:45:32 GMT</pubDate><title>Supreme Court faces new criticism for redistricting decision so close to 2026 elections</title><updateDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 16:45:32 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Alexandra Marquez</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Adam Wollner</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:32:35 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Omaha businessman Scott Petersen on Tuesday defeated Nebraska Secretary of State Bob Evnen in a Republican primary election, toppling a two-term incumbent by raising questions on the campaign trail about election integrity and ballot security</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/nebraska-secretary-state-loses-gop-primary-challenger-questioning-elec-rcna344905</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/nebraska-secretary-state-loses-gop-primary-challenger-questioning-elec-rcna344905</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260513-Bob-Evnen-ch-0932-09155c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Nati Harnik</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Bob Evnen.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Nebraska Secretary of State Bob Evnen lost in a Republican primary Tuesday night.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260513-Bob-Evnen-ch-0932-09155c.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:32:35 GMT</pubDate><title>Nebraska secretary of state loses GOP primary to challenger questioning election security</title><updateDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 14:32:35 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Minyvonne Burke</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Shelley Osterloh</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Doha Madani</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:00:19 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Utah grief author convicted of murder after prosecutors said she laced her husband’s cocktail with a fatal dose of fentanyl was sentenced to life in prison without parole on what would have been his 44th birthday.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/utah-grief-author-convicted-husbands-poisoning-death-sentenced-rcna344887</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/utah-grief-author-convicted-husbands-poisoning-death-sentenced-rcna344887</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/2360316-kouri-richins-mn-1130-9ef0a7.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Spenser Heaps</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Kouri Richins Murder Trial</media:text><media:description type="plain">Kouri Richins during her murder trial at the Summit County Courthouse in Park City, Utah, in February.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/2360316-kouri-richins-mn-1130-9ef0a7.jpg" height="1666" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 15:00:19 GMT</pubDate><title>Utah grief author sentenced to life in prison in husband’s poisoning death</title><updateDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 21:11:41 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jared Perlo</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Wed, 13 May 2026 09:30:42 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>OpenEvidence, an AI-powered medical search tool, has become a fast friend to America’s doctors and is now used by nearly two-thirds of physicians.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/openevidence-ai-doctor-medical-physician-login-app-what-npi-uptodate-rcna341064</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/openevidence-ai-doctor-medical-physician-login-app-what-npi-uptodate-rcna341064</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260512-doctors-ai-v2-cs-baa846.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1600" width="2400"><media:credit>Raven Jiang for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A patient lies in a hospital bed with a pick line attached to their arm, which is connected to a glowing computer chip that is connected to various IV bags and medical screens.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Most U.S. doctors are using OpenEvidence to inform medical decision-making.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-jeremy-cauwels-lr-baf492.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="3200" width="2400"><media:credit>Courtesy Sanford Health</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Jeremy Cauwels</media:text><media:description type="plain">Most U.S. doctors are using OpenEvidence to inform medical decision-making.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260422-open-evidence-homepage-lr-afc389.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1844" width="2550"><media:credit></media:credit><media:text type="plain">OpenEvidence looks similar to many mainstream AI platforms, but tuned for medicine.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Most U.S. doctors are using OpenEvidence to inform medical decision-making.</media:descr